\sqrt{(x+a/2)^2+h^2}+\sqrt{(x-a/2)^2+h^2}=k.\tag{$1$}
\frac{2ax}{\sqrt{(x+a/2)^2+h^2}-\sqrt{(x-a/2)^2+h^2}}=k.
\sqrt{(x+a/2)^2+h^2}-\sqrt{(x-a/2)^2+h^2}=\frac{2ax}{k}.\tag{$2$}
2\sqrt{(x+a/2)^2+h^2}=k+\frac{2ax}{k}.
